The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 22 September is 296,519 (34,175.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 17 September, there were 440 new confirmed cases (50.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 10 September, there were 379 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 16% (61 extra cases).
